subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis. Parthenogenetic female.
Body subovoid to triangular-ovoid, maximum height in posterior half, dorsal margin almost straight in posterior part, postero-dorsal angle distinct, posterior margin without 'step' in ventral portion (
Figs 112
, 
194–196
). No coarse striation on valves, fine striation delicate (
Figs 198, 200
). Head small, compound eye small, ocellus always bigger than eye (
Fig. 113
). PP = 2.5–4 IP, lateral head pores about 1.2 IP distance from midline (
Figs 197–198
). Labral keel subquadrangular, posterior margin with a single tuft of setules basally, anterior margin with long fringe of setules from base to apex, also five lateral groups of setules on sides (
Fig. 199
). Setae at middle of ventral margin of valve with long setules, short setules between their bases (
Fig. 201
). In posterior portion of the margin, setae asymmetrically setulated, posteriormost seta long. Submarginal setules of ventral portion of posterior margin short, fine, in continuous row; in middle of margin, robust, long, and sparse (
Fig. 202
). Marginal membrane with minute 'setules' (
Fig. 203
).

Abdomen with dorsal projection basally and a row of stout setules on distal margin of second segment (
Figs 204, 206
). Postabdomen subovoid, elongate (
Figs 114
, 
205–206
), with regularly convex ventral margin, preanal margin markedly longer than anus, in general convex, with numerous small hillocks, preanal and postanal angles well defined, small distal margin present (
Fig. 115
). Postanal marginal denticles in about 19–22 clusters, no marginal denticles on anal margin. About 10 fascicles of stout lateral setae, 2–5 setae in each fascicle, marginalmost setae of each fascicle significantly larger than the rest, 3–4 times as long as second seta, next 1–3 setae, if present, fine (
Figs 207–209
). About 12–14 fascicles of lateral setules on basal half of postanal and anal margin. Postabdominal claw long, slightly curved in distal half or straight, no setules at base, basal spine rudimentary, but seems to be always present (
Figs 210–211
).

Antenna I stout, not reaching tip of rostrum, with 4 transverse rows of long setules on anterior face, and analogous series on lateral and posterior face, no setules at end (
Figs 212–213
). Sensory seta arising about 1/4 of way from distal end. Largest aesthetasc half as long as appendage, reaching tip of rostrum. Antenna II with 3 long and stout spine-like setules on first, and 3–4 of these setules on second endopod segment (
Fig. 214
). Apical swimming setae with basal and distal segments unilaterally armed with stout, long setules, minute setules along other side of distal segment, no chitinous insertions within distal segments (
Fig. 215
). Basal and lateral seta subequal in size, both shorter than apical setae.

Trunk limb I (
Fig. 216
) with ODL large, bearing three series of fine setules and a long seta with unilaterally setulated distal segment. IDL with 4 medial clusters of fine setules, and 3 marginal clusters of short, robust setules. First IDL seta small, with numerous minute setules distally; second and third setae unequal in length and setulation (
Fig. 217
). Endite 3 with long seta 1 and small receptor near base, endite 2 with two longer soft setae (e–f) subequal in length, seta 2 naked, with long sensullum near base. Two ejector hooks of subequal size. Trunk limb II with exopodite ovoid, small, with tuft of short setules, eight scrapers (in one atypical female 9 scrapers were found, see 
Fig. 218
), distalmost scraper with naked basal segment, on distal lobe with basal tuft of long setules, distalmost seta in filter plate with inflated basal segment. Trunk limb III with trapezium-shaped exopodite, with four setae and small rudiment of seta 3, seta 2 with distal segment setulated bilaterally with short setules, filter plate with distalmost and basalmost setae smaller than others. Trunk limb IV with subovoid exopodite, with six setae, setae 2 long, seta 1 short, both armed with long, fine setules (
Fig. 221
); filter plate with distalmost seta with greatly inflated basal portion, all setae with inflated tips. Trunk limb V with semi-circular exopodite, on inner face of limb, a rudimentary, setulated seta and slender, unilaterally setulated seta, distal armature of gnathobase as lobe (
Figs 222
–223).
